WATCHES AND WARNINGS
--------------------
There are no coastal watches or warnings in effect.

Interests in Hawaii should monitor the progress of Calvin.


DISCUSSION AND OUTLOOK
----------------------
At 500 PM HST (0300 UTC), the center of Hurricane Calvin was located
near latitude 14.2 North, longitude 126.0 West. Calvin is moving
toward the west-northwest near 16 mph (26 km/h), and this general
motion is expected to continue for the next several days.

Maximum sustained winds are now near 120 mph (195 km/h) with higher
gusts.  Calvin is a category 3 hurricane on the Saffir-Simpson
Hurricane Wind Scale.  Weakening is forecast during the next couple 
of days.

Hurricane-force winds extend outward up to 35 miles (55 km) from the
center and tropical-storm-force winds extend outward up to 115 miles
(185 km).

The estimated minimum central pressure is 958 mb (28.29 inches).


